      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"choice\" to keep a story going feels so irrational. if we know the house always wins and the game is rigged to end in nothing, why stay at the table? it feels more like a trap than a choice. if the only reason to exist is a fake story, doesn't it actually make more sense to just opt out early? like, if it's all meaningless, there's no \"wrong\" way to handle it, right?",
